---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout title="Cookie Policy - Rhymance" pageTitle="Cookie Policy" lastUpdated="December 21, 2030">
	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			1. What are cookies?
		</h2>
		<p>
			Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device
			(computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website.
			Cookies allow the website to remember your actions and preferences
			(such as login, language, font size, and other display preferences)
			over a period of time, so you don't have to keep re-entering them
			whenever you come back to the site or browse from one page to another.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			2. How do we use cookies?
		</h2>
		<p>
			At Rhymance we use cookies to improve your user experience,
			understand how you interact with our application,
			and optimize our services. Cookies help us to:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>Keep you signed in while you browse the application</li>
			<li>Remember your preferences and personal settings</li>
			<li>Analyze the use of our application to improve its functionality</li>
			<li>Provide personalized content based on your interests</li>
			<li>Ensure the security of your account</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			3. Types of cookies we use
		</h2>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			3.1 Strictly necessary cookies
		</h3>
		<p>
			These cookies are essential for you to browse the website and use its features.
			Without these cookies, we could not provide services you have asked for,
			such as accessing secure areas of the website or making transactions.
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Session cookies:</strong> Allow you to keep your session active while using Rhymance</li>
			<li><strong>Authentication cookies:</strong> Verify your identity when you log in</li>
			<li><strong>Security cookies:</strong> Protect against fraudulent activities and keep your account safe</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			3.2 Performance cookies
		</h3>
		<p>
			These cookies collect information about how visitors use a website,
			for instance which pages visitors go to most often,
			and if they get error messages. These cookies don't collect information
			that identifies a visitor. All information these cookies collect is aggregated
			and therefore anonymous.
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Usage analysis:</strong> Help us understand which features are most popular</li>
			<li><strong>Error detection:</strong> Identify technical issues to improve app stability</li>
			<li><strong>Load optimization:</strong> Improve the speed and performance of the application</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			3.3 Functionality cookies
		</h3>
		<p>
			These cookies allow the website to remember choices you make
			(such as your user name, language or the region you are in)
			and provide enhanced, more personal features.
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>User preferences:</strong> Save your personal settings and preferences</li>
			<li><strong>Language and region:</strong> Remember your preferred language and location</li>
			<li><strong>Personalized content:</strong> Adapt the experience based on your musical interests</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			3.4 Advertising and social media cookies
		</h3>
		<p>
			These cookies are used to deliver adverts more relevant to you and your interests.
			They are also used to limit the number of times you see an advertisement
			as well as help measure the effectiveness of the advertising campaigns.
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Targeted advertising:</strong> Show relevant ads based on your interests</li>
			<li><strong>Advertising analysis:</strong> Measure the effectiveness of our campaigns</li>
			<li><strong>Social media:</strong> Allow you to share content on social platforms</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			4. Third-party cookies
		</h2>
		<p>
			In addition to our own cookies, we may also use various third-parties
			cookies to report usage statistics of the application,
			deliver advertisements on and through the application, and so on.
		</p>
		<p>
			Third parties that may set cookies through Rhymance include:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> For traffic and user behavior analysis</li>
			<li><strong>Advertising services:</strong> To show personalized ads</li>
			<li><strong>Social media platforms:</strong> To allow social media integration</li>
			<li><strong>Content providers:</strong> To offer additional functionalities</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			Please note that we have no control over these third-party cookies.
			We recommend that you check the third-party websites for more
			information about their cookies and how to manage them.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			5. Cookie duration
		</h2>
		<p>The cookies we use can be:</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>
				<strong>Session cookies:</strong> These are temporary and are
				deleted when you close your browser or application.
				They are mainly used to keep your session active.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Persistent cookies:</strong> Remain on your device
				for a set period of time or until you delete them manually.
				They are used to remember your preferences and improve
				your experience on future visits.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			The duration of our persistent cookies varies depending on their
			purpose, but generally does not exceed 12 months.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			6. Cookie management
		</h2>
		<p>
			You have the right to decide whether to accept or reject cookies.
			You can exercise your cookie preferences through the following options:
		</p>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			6.1 Browser settings
		</h3>
		<p>
			Most web browsers allow some control of most cookies through
			the browser settings. To find out more about cookies,
			including how to see what cookies have been set and how
			to manage and delete them, visit:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>
				<strong>Google Chrome:</strong>
				<a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Chrome cookie settings</a>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong>
				<a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Firefox cookie settings</a>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Safari:</strong>
				<a href="https://support.apple.com/guide/safari/manage-cookies-and-website-data-sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Safari cookie settings</a>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong>
				<a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Edge cookie settings</a>
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			6.2 Application settings
		</h3>
		<p>
			Within Rhymance settings, you can manage your cookie preferences
			in the "Privacy and Security" section. There you can:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>Accept or reject non-essential cookies</li>
			<li>See which cookies are currently active</li>
			<li>Delete previously stored cookies</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold mb-2 mt-4">
			6.3 Opt-out tools
		</h3>
		<p>
			For advertising cookies, you can opt out by visiting:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Your Online Choices</a></li>
			<li><a href="https://www.networkadvertising.org/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Network Advertising Initiative</a></li>
			<li><a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-white hover:underline">Digital Advertising Alliance</a></li>
		</ul>

		<p class="mt-3">
			<strong>Important:</strong> Please note that blocking or deleting
			cookies may affect your user experience and some features of Rhymance
			may not function properly. Some cookies are strictly necessary for
			our application to work.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			7. Cookies on mobile devices
		</h2>
		<p>
			If you access Rhymance through our mobile application, we use
			similar technologies to cookies to collect information and
			improve your experience. These technologies include:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li><strong>Device identifiers:</strong> To uniquely recognize your device</li>
			<li><strong>Third-party SDKs:</strong> For analytics and additional functionality</li>
			<li><strong>Local storage:</strong> To save preferences and application data</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			You can manage these technologies through your mobile device's
			privacy settings or within the Rhymance application settings.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			8. Updates to this policy
		</h2>
		<p>
			We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time in order to
			reflect, for example, changes to the cookies we use or for other
			operational, legal or regulatory reasons. Please therefore
			re-visit this Cookie Policy regularly to stay informed about
			our use of cookies.
		</p>
		<p>
			The "Last updated" date at the top of this policy indicates when
			it was last revised. Any changes to this policy will become
			effective when we post the revised policy on our website or
			application.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			9. More information
		</h2>
		<p>
			If you have any questions about our Cookie Policy or how we use
			cookies, please feel free to contact us:
		</p>
		<ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
			<li>
				<strong>Email:</strong>
				<a href="mailto:luismarrer.dev@gmail.com" class="text-white hover:underline">luismarrer.dev@gmail.com</a>
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Contact form:</strong>
				<a href="/contact" class="text-white hover:underline">Contact page</a>
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>
			You can also review our <a href="/privacy" class="text-white hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> to learn more about how we protect your personal information.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mb-5">
		<h2 class="text-white text-xl font-bold mb-3">
			10. Consent
		</h2>
		<p>
			By continuing to use Rhymance, you consent to the use of cookies
			in accordance with this Cookie Policy. If you do not agree to our
			use of cookies, you should adjust your browser settings accordingly
			or refrain from using our website or application.
		</p>
		<p>
			For cookies that require your consent, we will provide you with a
			cookie banner the first time you visit Rhymance, where you can
			accept or reject non-essential cookies.
		</p>
	</section>
</LegalLayout>
